article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 66, Cent. Connecticut St. 60
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Cameron Tyler scored 21 points and grabbed seven rebounds as Fairleigh Dickinson overcame a poor first half and rallied to beat Central Connecticut State 66-60 on Saturday night. Andre Harris added 16 points and Michael Peeples finished with 10 points and 11 rebounds for the Knights (14-12, 9-6 in Northeast Conference). Obie Nwadike led the Blue Devils (17-11, 14-2) with 27 points and 17 rebounds, while Javier Mojica finished with 10 points and Tristan Blackwood added nine points and seven assists. The Blue Devils appeared ready to run away with the game early on, scoring the first seven points while FDU missed their first six shots and turned the ball over three times in the first four minutes. Central Connecticut then expanded its lead to as much as 16 points and led 34-21 at halftime. The Blue Devils stayed hot early on in the second half, stretching the lead to 40-25 before the Knights started their comeback with a 15-3 run to cut the lead to 43-40 with 10:30 remaining. Nwadike then hit two free throws, but the Knights then went on a 13-0 run to take the lead for good. Central Connecticut tried to rally late, cutting the lead to 62-55 with 1:29 to play, but FDU sealed the win by making 4-of-7 free throws down the stretch.
